Version (1.1.6)
Released 2002.07.15

	- The compass can display a different graphic to display if a
	  player has already visited the room a direction leads to
	- The compass can display a different graphic to indicate the last
	  direction a player traveled from
	- Objects can be manipulated directly through their Close Up Images


Version (1.1.5)
Released 2002.06.20

	- GUI Interaction with Objects on the Graphic Panel
	- Audio support added to Events
	- Threaded Text-To-Speech under Windows
	- Improved Text-To-Speech under Linux
	- Save functionality restored under GTK+/SDL
	- Word-Wrapping Enabled for all GtkText Widgets
	- Better Text-Only Interface support


Version (1.1.4)
Released 2002.06.16

	- Complete GUI-based interaction
	- Graphical Mouse Pointers
	- Scrollable Inventory and Object Panels


Version (1.1.3)
Released 2002.06.09

	- Graphical Inventory
	- Graphical Object Panel
	- Updated PyGTK support under Win32
	- Uses new ".cog" file format
	- Miscellaneous Bugfixes


Version (1.1.2)
Released 2002.05.30

	- Text-To-Speech Synthesis added under Linux and Windows
	- Passive Graphical Compass added to GTK+/SDL Frontend
	- Better OOP reorganizations


Version (1.1.1)
Released 2002.05.15

	- New GtkSDL version of the Cog Engine (independant release)
	- New Jython Applet version of the Cog Engine (replaces 1.0 Java version)
	- Beginnings of PyUI based version of the Cog Engine
	- Image Layering fixed in the Cog Engine
	- Large amounts of code restructuring and modularization
	- Many minor bugfixes


Version (1.0)
Released 2002.01.26

	- Fixed bug in GraphicPanel that try to paint images which had not
	  downloaded correctly.


Version (0.95)
Released 2001.09.22

	- "Image Directory" variable added. This makes it easier to use
	  the same game data with different graphics files. For instance,
	  if you have a high and a low resolution version of the same
	  game, you only have to change this entry to point to another
	  directory, and the rest of the game data remains intact.

	- Inventory display adjusted to now display an "(eqipped)" tag on
	  the end of all listed equipped items

	- If an obstruction was marked visible but didn't have a graphic,
	  it's name would not get printed to the output area. This has
	  been fixed.

	- CogEngine updated to skip introduction when started with a
	  current room number greater than one (will be useful when saving
	  and loading games becomes available)
